Australia Newcastle Thermal Coal Rises 4% to $131.71 a Ton

-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 
2011-02-25T12:37:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/australia-newcastle-thermal-coal-rises-4-to-131-71-a-ton.html
Power-station coal  prices  at
Australia’s Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, rose 4 percent
in the week ended today.  Coal prices at the New South Wales port climbed to $131.71
a metric ton from $126.64 the previous week, according to the
 globalCOAL NEWC Index .    Xstrata Plc , the world’s largest exporter of power-station
coal, BHP Billiton Ltd. and Rio Tinto Group are among mining
companies that ship coal through Newcastle.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pratish Narayanan in Mumbai at 
 pnarayanan9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Clyde Russell at 
 crussell7@bloomberg.net  